  "texts": [
    "Our traditional template of seeking to identify and credit a key 'author' often leads us to gloss over different contributions to settle on one convenient name: but this practice is to the detriment of clarity and fairly attributing credit for contributions made.",
    "Cases of text creation involving AI increasingly disrupt this traditional template and encourage us to consider the specific contributions of each agent and entity, in similar ways to efforts currently advocated by some in scientific research [12,77,79]-although these, too, currently refuse to acknowledge AI's contributions on par with that of humans.",
    "Marketing copyLLMs also increasingly drive the accelerated production of marketing materials.",
    "In this space, now-familiar questions about creatorship again arise: who should be considered a creator of marketing copy and promotional content produced with LLMs?",
    "Can users simply use outputs straightforwardly for commercial purposes without acknowledging the role of LLMs in their production, or indeed, that of other actors?"
  ],
